## MCP Tools

The Databricks MCP server is configured per-project in `.mcp.json`. When available, use these tools to execute work directly on Databricks rather than generating code for the user to run:

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `mcp__databricks__execute_sql` | Run SQL against a warehouse |
| `mcp__databricks__run_python_file_on_databricks` | Run a Python file on a cluster |
| `mcp__databricks__upload_file` | Upload a file to the workspace |
| `mcp__databricks__upload_folder` | Upload a folder to the workspace |
| `mcp__databricks__create_or_update_pipeline` | Create or update a DLT pipeline |
| `mcp__databricks__start_update` | Start a pipeline update |
| `mcp__databricks__get_update` | Get pipeline update status |
| `mcp__databricks__get_pipeline` | Get pipeline details |
| `mcp__databricks__get_pipeline_events` | Get pipeline events/logs |
| `mcp__databricks__delete_pipeline` | Delete a pipeline |
| `mcp__databricks__execute_sql_multi` | Run multiple SQL statements |

